An engineer registers a Python UDF in Snowpark:

```python
@udf(name='clean_phone', is_permanent=True, stage_location='@udf_stage', session=session)
def clean_phone(phone: str) -> str:
    import re
    return re.sub(r'[^\d]', '', phone)
```

Where does this function execute when called inside a Snowflake query?
